    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - BODY FEATURES - HEATED MIRRORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290123">
        <title>HEATED MIRRORS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f08290916">heated mirror function diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f08290916" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08290916.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Heated Mirror Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. HEATED MIRRORS</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LEFT HAND SWITCH PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>This function controls the heated mirrors. The mirrors turn on and off with the appropriate panel
                mounted, momentary switch. This feature will only work when the ignition is ON.
            </para>
            <para>The heated mirror switch is located in the left hand instrument panel. When selected, the switch will
                close a circuit that will provide power to the heated mirrors.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
